  "target_response": {
    "text": "Strain measures cardiovascular load: how much time your heart spent working above its easy zones today, compressed onto a 0 to 21 scale where each additional point gets harder to earn. It counts heart-time, not effort-feel — which is exactly why some days read higher yet feel the same, since lifting, heat, or stress change how hard a session feels without changing time-in-zone much. Today's strain of 11.3 sits right in your own middle: your 7-day average strain is 12.1 and your 30-day mean is 12.6, so this was an ordinary day's load by your standards, not a light one. One calibration note: strain here is an estimate built from heart-rate data, so treat single-day differences of a point or two as noise. The useful comparison is your week against your month — not today against somebody else's number.",
